{
  "text": "3. What is the smallest t such that if G is embedded on S g , then \u03c7 s (G) = O(g t )? We know that 4/7 \u2264 t \u2264 1 (see [CITATION_1] and Theorem 5.4).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "121441445"
